@startuml
title USB Verification: Speed vs Stability (速度 vs 安定性)

actor "User" as user
participant "C100P (Host)" as host
participant "zram (Compressed RAM)" as zram
participant "SanDisk 2.0 (Stable)" as usb_stable
participant "Cheap 3.0 (Unstable)" as usb_unstable

== Case A: Random Access Bottleneck (ランダムアクセスのボトルネック) ==
user -> host: Execute task (タスク実行)
host -> usb_unstable: Write small logs (小さなログを書き込み)
note over usb_unstable: High Latency (大きな遅延発生)
usb_unstable --/ host: I/O Wait (応答待ち)
host -> host: **System Stuttering / Petit-freeze** (プチフリ発生)

== Case B: Optimization with zram (zramによる最適化) ==
user -> host: Execute task (タスク実行)
host -> zram: Write temporary data (一時データの書き込み)
note over zram: Fast Compression / zstd (高速圧縮)
zram -> host: Instant Response (即座に応答)

host -> usb_stable: Stable background write (安定したバックグラウンド書き込み)
note over usb_stable: Low Throughput but Reliable (速度は低いが信頼できる)
usb_stable -> host: Task Completed (タスク完了)
note right: **Smooth Performance!** (快適な動作！)

@enduml